w = watt – defines the watt quantity to charge
p =  price – define the charge price for the total duration / watts selected (*charges the total amount regardless if not total time used)
TP = Tier Pricing

Attribute defines the string in a specific format to allow definition of several tier prices (allows flexibility to define more than 2 tier prices) String format: example: m60u60p0,m360u60p300,m480u60p350 (tiers separated by comma) m = minutes – defines the duration of tier range (sum of all tiers will define max time) u = unit type for charge if value = number (int) then defines the time unit per charge price

if value = W then charge price will be by kWH p = price charge per unit type

Meter Value Clock Align Interval defines the time interval in seconds to send meter value no matter if there is a charging session or not. 
The best practice is 15, 30, 60 minutes, or duplication of 60 minutes. 
If 15, send it at XX:00, XX:15, XX:30, XX:45, no meter when the charger starts working.
